node.text: Some of your favorite @TikTok creators are coming to @AirbnbExperiences. Go behind the scenes and learn their secrets of self-expression—right from home. Work out with @trevorbell, take better photos with @bonnierzm, make home videos with @itsthemcfarlands, dance with choreographer @arbengiga and more. Link in bio.

node.text: Happy Mother’s Day from Miami baker and @airbnbexperiences host, @laromibakery. Originally from Argentina, she’ll show you how to make traditional alfajores that are sure to sweeten up Mom’s day. For as beautiful as these dulce de leche sandwich cookies turn out, they’re surprisingly simple to make. Follow Romina’s foolproof recipe or join her Online Experience to make a sweet suite of Latin desserts. Link in bio.

node.text: Happy Mother’s Day from Nashville-based singer-songwriter and @airbnbexperiences host, @annebucklemusic. Follow Anne’s simple tricks for crafting a tune, or join her Online Experience for live instruction and melody-making. Link in bio.

node.text:
In March, @AirbnbExperiences hosts all over the world had to stop doing what they love—sharing their interests and passions with others. 
Over the past few weeks, they’ve offered ideas for how to continue hosting even while we’re apart. 
They’ve adapted recipes based on what’s in their pantries, turned living rooms into yoga studios, and choreographed dances for families at home.

Today we’re excited to announce that Airbnb Experiences are now online. You can take a flamenco class with Lidón in Madrid, participate in a tarot card reading with Mak in Austin, or visit a colony of penguins in Cape Town—all from home.

True to Airbnb Experiences in real life, Online Experiences are hosted by remarkable people and set in small groups. Alongside making a new dish, maybe you’ll make a new friend, too.

Thank you to our incredible hosts around the world. We’ll see you online soon —> link in bio.

node.text:
The veranda is bound to be your favorite room at Superhost Paul’s mountain villa. The only question is which you’ll prefer: its coziness on mornings like this or the view once the mist burns off. If the day gets hot, follow the river to a waterfall for a bracing dip. 

Link in bio for misty mountain retreat. 

Video: @villadelpino77

node.text:
Superhost David’s sprawling ’70s villa is perfect for a long, leisurely good time with a dozen or so of your best friends. Hit a different nearby beach every day (don’t miss the caves of Praia dos Três Irmãos) or just sit around the pool eating the tangerines and cherimoyas you’ve just picked from the orchard. 

Link in bio for laid-back luxury. 

Photos: @_a_pausa_

node.text:
You might spend your first hour at Superhost Jayna’s house switching between the ocean views and all her custom tile and stained-glass design touches. Once the whiplash subsides, settle in for a serene retreat or head out for a day of horseback riding or sport fishing. 

Link in bio for Baja beauty.

Photo: @jonathanjacobs89

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb on August 09, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Waking up in a majestic, centuries-old villa in the Santa Monica Mountains is even sweeter when you know you won’t be going home ahead of schedule. Better known as “The Mansion,” Superhost Nick’s sprawling estate features one of the most famous pools in the world, but you might find yourself spending more time exploring the nearby vineyards and canyons.

Link in bio to accept this rose.

Photos: @villadelavina and @garrettrichardson

node.text:
Superhosts Beth and Ben apparently didn’t think a solar-powered barrel house was unique enough, so they floated it on Fox Creek. After a day of exploring the vineyards along Lake Erie’s north shore, take your rowboat out for a romantic evening cruise (or to try to catch your dinner). 

Link in bio to give in to pier pressure.

Photos: @utterlyuncorked

node.text:
This tiny jungle villa is far from the crowds but still within easy reach of the action, whether that means world-class surfing at Cloud 9 or a bowl of kinilaw alongside a skate bowl at CEV. Or you can just linger or on the white sand beach a hundred steps away. 

Link in bio for swells and solitude. 

Photo: @bombora.siargao

node.text:
The area’s hot springs have drawn distant visitors for centuries, but you won’t need to go farther than your balcony for a springwater soak. Eriko, your history-loving Superhost, will also point you toward her favorite nearby places, including Odawara Castle. 

Link in bio to wishlist.

node.text:
The hoops action doesn’t have to stop when the Olympics end. Whether you’re looking to perfect your Euro step in private or finally settle that long-running one-on-one rivalry, you can hold court in homes like a sprawling Arizona estate or a Costa Rican villa high above the Pacific.

Link in bio to call next.

node.text:
From the boulders of the Mojave to the jagged peaks of the Dolomites, find your way to homes and experiences that give you something to climb before you climb into bed. If you need a little inspiration to reach the next level, the Mawem brothers (@lesfreresmawemofficiel) from the French Olympic team have shared a wishlist that’ll take you to new heights.

Link in bio to elevate yourself.

Link in bio to get a grip.

Link in bio to dive into this refreshing list.
